Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Lightly oil a #baking sheet{}. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and quarter @sweet potatoes{1} lengthwise; cut into ½-inch-thick pieces. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Trim and cut @scallions{2} into 1-inch pieces.

In a #large bowl{}, soak @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup} with 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4); let stand until absorbed (you'll use in the next step).

Toss sweet potato, ginger, and @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} on one side of prepared sheet with a drizzle of oil and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

Meanwhile, to bowl with panko mixture, add @ground beef{10%ounce}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @onion powder{1%tablespoon}, salt (we used ¾ tsp; 1¼ tsp for 4), and pepper and gently mix to combine.

Form into 6 evenly sized meatballs (12 meatballs for 4).

> Swap in beef for pork.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Once sweet potato has roasted 5 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Place meatballs on opposite side of sheet. (For 4 servings, add meatballs to a second sheet.)

Carefully add green beans and scallions to sweet potato; toss to combine.

Return to top rack and roast until meatballs are cooked through, ~{11%minutes}. (For 4, roast meatballs on middle rack and veggies on top rack, swapping positions halfway through.)

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, mix @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon} and @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon} until combined.

Once veggies and meatballs have cooked 11 minutes, remove sheet from oven. (For 4 servings, leave veggies roasting on middle rack.)

Carefully brush meatballs with hoisin glaze. Return to top rack until glaze is tacky and veggies are tender, ~{3-5%minutes} more.

Divide gingery sweet potato and green bean jumble between shallow bowls; top with hoisin-glazed meatballs. Serve.